	<text>
		<body>
			<p><!--R. Legation of Italy Cable No. 2836/1306 Addressed to R. Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Rome
        [Six incoming mail stamps, some barely legible, dated between 13th and possibly 16th August
        1941]--></p>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19410806-IT_01.jpg"/>
			<p><placeName ref="www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html">Budapest</placeName>, 6th August 1941, Year XIX</p>
			<p>Re: <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Jews</term> against the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Hungary</placeName></p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">military</term> action against <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russia</placeName> and the occupation by <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungarian</placeName> troops of a considerable part of the territory of
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/562153/galicia.html">Galicia</placeName> has offered Authorities here the opportunity to
				solve a problem that had arisen during and after the operations carried out by <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>. A large number of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term> elements had been able to filter in from
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> and in some cases also from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russian</placeName> territory and, with the support of
				coreligionists living in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungary</placeName>, had managed to live here
				practically undisturbed until now. These past weeks the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html"
					>Hungarian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> has carried out raids against the
				said <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Semitic</term> elements who, in concert with
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungarian</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">German</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">military</term> authorities, have then been
				conveyed to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/562153/galicia.html">Galicia</placeName>, particularly to the major towns such as
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/705392/kolomyia.html">Kolomea</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/707471/ivano-frankivsk.html">Stanislau</placeName>, where they are assigned to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term>and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">employed</term> in excavation work, demolitions, mine
				clearance etc. So far, according to official information, the number of these <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> amounts to approx. 12,000, but this number
				will increase significantly as a recent decree has determined to extend the same measures to those <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> having <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName> or <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Soviet</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147" type="subject">citizenship</term><pb n="2"
					facs="EHRI-DR-19410806-IT_02.jpg"/> who, although they live in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html"
					>Hungary</placeName> with a proper residence permit, have not requested and obtained the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungarian</placeName> citizenship during the past ten years. The only difference
				between these latter and those who have entered <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Magyar</placeName>
				territory illegally will be, it is said, that they will be allowed to take their personal property with them, whereas the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> transported to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/562153/galicia.html">Galicia</placeName> up to now have been allowed to transfer only the sum of not
				more than 30 Pengö, equivalent to 120 Italian Lira. <persName ref="#ehri_dr_talamo_giuseppe">Talamo</persName>
			</p>
